title: build error: conflicting types for ‘cpuinfo_initialize’
body_html:
I got the codes by 'git clone' and tried 'python setup.py install'. Then, I got the following error:

.../download/pytorch/aten/src/ATen/cpu/cpuinfo/src/init.c:22:18: error: conflicting types for ‘cpuinfo_initialize’
 bool CPUINFO_ABI cpuinfo_initialize(void) {
                  ^
In file included from .../download/pytorch/aten/src/ATen/cpu/cpuinfo/src/init.c:7:0:
.../anaconda3/include/cpuinfo.h:491:18: note: previous declaration of ‘cpuinfo_initialize’ was here
 void CPUINFO_ABI cpuinfo_initialize(void);
  • OS: Ubuntu 16.04
  • PyTorch version: 0.4 (e9f144b)
  • How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): source ('git clone')
  • Python version: Python 3.6.4 |Anaconda custom (64-bit)| (default, Jan 16 2018, 18:10:19), [GCC 7.2.0] on linux
  • CUDA/cuDNN version: CUDA 9.0, cuDNN 7.0.5
  • GPU models and configuration: nVidia GTX 1080
  • GCC version (if compiling from source): 5.4.0 20160609
